                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.11/551: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1927-04-06T06:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 6, 1927—6 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received April 5—6:40 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>357. Following from American consul at Hankow: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“April 4, 5 p.m. Twelve Americans departed via <hi rend="italic"
                                >Woosung</hi> yesterday morning; 9 by the <hi rend="italic"
                                >Kian</hi> and 25 via <hi rend="italic">Woon Ho</hi> last night.
                            There remain here 89 men, 19 women and 12 children. Nearly all these are
                            sleeping aboard ships. Additional departures tomorrow or next day.
                            Admiral Hough<note n="16" xml:id="d302fn16">Rear Admiral Henry H. Hough,
                                U. S. N., commander of the Yangtze Patrol.</note> returned here this
                            morning.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
